column2: Clear sky- winds from the south
Clear sky- west winds- particles suspended in water- brownish tinge color.
Particles in suspension in water- sunny skies- calm water.
North winds at 5 mph- no particles- rain during the week- 2.3 inches.
Sky- high thin clouds.  No particles in the water.
Winds are calm. sky is clear.
Wind: 10 mph from the west- sky: tested during a break in the clouds.
Wind: 10 mph from the west- sky: clear- reading fluctuated during test- sometimes varying 1-2 feet.  Heavy rains on 9/6/92.
Sky- is clear.  Wind- is 5-10 mph e.  Particles in the water- anchor came up clean as always.
Sky is clear- wind from the south @ 10 mph- particles in the water.
Wind @ 10 mph northeast- sky is clear- particles in the water- anchor came up clean.
Sky- high thin clouds- wind is west @ 10 mph- particles in water.
Sky is clear- winds are 10-15 mph from north.  Anchor came up clean.
Clear sky- calm winds- anchor came up clean.
Clear sky- no wind- anchor came up clean
Clear sky- S wind 5-10mph- suspended particles in water- 1.72" of rain in last 4 days
Suspended particles in water- clear sky- W wind 5-10mph- 2 eaglets in nest - adult nearby
Mostly sunny- white- fluffy clouds- 48 degrees.
Small clouds building- breezy- air temp 55 F at 7 am- 65 at 10: 30.
Calm wind- clear sky- two eaglets near nest- calling (presumably) for food- 1st test on 8/7
Wind: south @ 5 mph- sky: high thin clouds- adult eagle is near the nest- no sign of eaglets.
Skies clear- 50 degrees @ 7 am- breezy- .25" of rain yesterday afternoon.
Eaglet flapping wings-adult near by- particles in water- clear sky- west wind 5 mph.
Wind-5 mph from south.  Sky-test during break in clouds.
Test during break in clouds.  West wind @ 5 mph.
West wind 10 mph.  Test during break in clouds. eaglet in nest.
Sky clear.  Wind 10 mph west.  Eaglet + parent eagle above nest (eaglet has not flown yet).
Calm water- clear sky- eaglet in nest with 2 adults nearby.
Clear sky- west wind 15 mph- eaglet in nest was seen to fly last weekend.
Clear sky- wind is S 5-10 mph- clarity varies due to under current- recovered 4.65" rain in the last 4 days.
No sign of eagle today- clear sky- winds are calm.  Bottom stirred from gull lake out flow.
Clear sky- south wind -10 mph- Rippley current from gull lake- brown furry mink-like animal on the rocks of Falk-gull bridge.
High thin haze- bright sun- light breeze.  Temp is 45 degrees- sludge on the anchor.
Ice out 4/21- bright- hazy- and the wind is calm.
2.3" of rain since last test on 5/6.  South wind is 5 mph.  Clear sky.
North wind at 5-10 mph- sky has high thin clouds.  It rained .14" since last week.
Clear sky- north wind at 5 mph- 1-2" since last test- some sludge on anchor- two eagles in nest flapping their wings.
North wind at 5 mph- test between clouds- eaglets in nest with their parent nearby- 1" of rain since last test.
Bright and hazy.  Few small puffy cloudy- the temperature is 68 degrees at 7: 00am- the secchi test done earlier under clear skies.
High thin clouds- south wind 5 mph- sludge on anchor fluke- no rain in two weeks- eaglets in or neat nest.
High thin clouds- west wind a5 mph- no rain since last week- one eaglet flying to the nest-other standing on the nest.
Sky: high thin clouds- wind: south 5 mph- 2.25" rain since 7/7/95.
Clear sky- calm winds @ 65 mph- high on 7/15 was 65 degrees- high on 7/14 was 90's.
Clear sky- west wind 5 mph- 0.50" rain in last 24 hours + 1.10" since 7/14.  Two eaglets on branches near nest.
Rain=7.85" since 7/28/95.  Sky-clear.  Wind-west 10 to 15 mph.
Clear sky- winds calm- adult eagle sitting on branch near nest.
Temp 35 degrees at 7 am.  Eagles nesting- 5th year.
One to two foot waves in rapids under the bridge between Falk and Gulf lakes.  Clear sky.  West wind 10-15 mph.  Lake level: very high
Clear sky.  West wind about 5 mph.  Adult eagle perched on a branch near nest.
Clear sky.  Calm wind.  Pin head size or small particles in the water.  Some floating brown stuff.
5" rain two days ago.  Reading varies from undercurrent.  Clear sky.  Southwest wind 10 mph.
Clear sky.  Baby eagle.  Calm water.  Lake level: very high
Clear sky.  Southeast wind 10 mph.  Secchi readings vary due to current from gull lake.  1-2 inches of rain last month.  Lake level: very high
Clear sky.  South wind at 5-10 mph.  Eagles nest blown down in the storm last week!!
Clear sky.  North wind of 5 mph.
Eagles nest in tree flew over because of high winds- young still around.
Clear sky.  South wind about 10 mph.  Eagles still present even though nest was blown down.
Eagles have new nest- near the site of the one that blew done last august.
Rain gauge reading from 7/25/97- from 4 am to 9 am = 2.5 inches.
High thin clouds- W wind 5 mph.
Sky is clear- south wind at 10-15 mph- water is high- 2 eagles on nest
Lake is very calm today- sunny- temp is 56 degrees.
Lake level normal- no eagle today.
Adult eagle on nest- clear sky.
E wind 5 mph- high thin clouds- 2 adult eagles.
Calm- clear sky- particles in water. 2 eaglets.
2 young eagles standing on edge of nest.
Calm- clear sky- N wind 10 mph.
Clear sky. 10-15 mph south wind. eagles are nesting-8th year. adult on nest May be feeding young. cold water.
Clear sky. south wind 5 mph. adult eagle near nest. one eaglet in nest.
Clear sky and south wind 5 mph.
High thin clouds. E wind 5 mph. mud on one anchor fluke.
Test between clouds. northwest wind 5-10 mph. air temp in low 40's (cold hands).
Clear sky and north wind at 5-10 mph.
With grand nephew- Sam Vanwetter (age 6)- clear sky- west wind at 5 mph- 1.1" of rain in the last 24 hours.
Clear sky- west wind at 10 mph- and mud on anchor flukes.
South wind at 10 mph and clear sky.
North wind at 10 mph- clear sky between clouds- and one adult eagle and lone eaglet in nest.
South wind at 10 mph- clear sky- eaglet in nest- and adult loons and one baby loon.
Monitored with grand niece- Hannah Vanwetter.  Calm- clear sky- nesting barn swallow under bridge- and eaglet in nest.
Calm- clear sky- adult eagle near nest- and eaglet is gone.
Calm- clear sky- mud in anchor flukes- and no eagles.
Calm- clear sky- and an adult eagle on shore- flew in small tree.
West wind 10-15 mph. Clear sky. Adult eagle near nest.
North wind 10-15 mph. Clear between clouds. One loon swimming.
South wind 15 mph. Clear- hazy sky. Hot and humid. Mud on anchor flukes.
East wind 5 mph. Clear sky. Eagles nest blew down 7/8/02. Immature eagle nearby.
West wind 5 mph. Clear sky. About 30 geese between Falk and Love Lakes. Mud on anchor fluke.
Clear sky- calm. Particles in water. Purple Loosestrife near east point to Love Lake.
High thin clouds. South wind 10 mph. Mud on anchor fluke. 5.5 inches of rain last week.
Clear sky; north wind 10 mph. Mud on anchor flukes.
Reading corrected for 4 ft rail on pontoon.  Adult eagle in nest.  Calm- clear sky.
Rail correction.  SW wind 15-20 mph.  Clear sky.  Mud and weeds on anchor fluke.  Over 2" rain past week.
Rail correction.  SW wind 10 mph.  Clear sky.  Mud and weeds on anchor.
Rail correction.  Wind calm.  Clear sky.  Nest of barn swallows under bridge.  4-5 baby swallows.  Data collectors: Kent Dickerman- Marshall Thompson- Blaine Darrah and Toni Ventenbergs.
South wind 5 mph.  Clear sky.  45 geese swam by.  Immature eagle returning to nest.  Rail correction.
Test between clouds.  Wind calm.  Immature eagle near nest.  Rail correction.  Data collectors: Kent Dickerman and Sam- Sampson- Jesse- Jared- Isabella- John- Chris
Lots of geese swimming.  South wind 5 mph.  Clear sky.  Immature eagle at nest.  Rail correction.
Calm- clear- 4 ft to surface rail correction.
West wind 1- mph.  Test between clouds.  Mud on anchor flukes.
South wind 15 mph.  Clear sky.  19 goslings and 9 adult geese swimming.  Mud on flukes of anchor.
East wind 5 mph.  Clear sky.  3 loons swimming.
50 geese.  Clear sky.  South wind 15 mph.  Dragged anchor.  Baby swallow in nest under bridge.
South wind 5 mph.  Clear sky.  One adult eagle flying.
South wind 10-15 mph.  High thin clouds.
South wind 5-10 mph.  Mud on anchor flukes.  Clear sky.
Clear sky.  South wind 10 mph.  Weeds on anchor flukes.  2 adult eagles catching thermals.

Mark Bixby was my helper. It was a windy day. Mark Bixby was my helper. It was a windy day.

Pleasant day in a delayed spring with scattered clouds. There had been rain the night before- the blueberries were in bloom. Mark Bixby accompanied me. Beaufort 3- temp 65 degrees F.
Hot summer day- a bit hazy because of wildfires to west- still. Some boat activity. Accompanied by Mark Bixby and Tina Juliana and Angel Hillstrom
Scattered clouds- calm but some boat traffic. 85 degrees. Mark Bixby is my helper. Scaattered clouds- calm- 85 degrees. Mark Bixby is my helper.
High haze- light breeze- scattered cirrostratus clouds
